3. INNER JOIN Objective  
Retrieve only customers who have placed orders.  
SQL Query  
SELECT Customers.CustomerID,  
Customers.CustomerName,  
Orders.OrderID,  
Orders.Product,  
Orders.Amount  
FROM Customers  
INNER JOIN Orders  
ON Customers.CustomerID = Orders.CustomerID; 

4. LEFT JOIN Objective  
Retrieve all customers, including those who have not placed any orders.  
SQL Query  
SELECT Customers.CustomerID,  
Customers.CustomerName,  
Orders.OrderID,  
Orders.Product  
FROM Customers  
LEFT JOIN Orders  
ON Customers.CustomerID = Orders.CustomerID; 


5. RIGHT JOIN Objective  
Retrieve all orders, including orders without matching customers.  
SQL Query  
SELECT Customers.CustomerName,  
Orders.OrderID,  
Orders.Product  
FROM Customers  
RIGHT JOIN Orders  
ON Customers.CustomerID = Orders.CustomerID; 

6. FULL OUTER JOIN Objective  
Retrieve all customers and all orders, even if no match exists.  
SQL Query  
SELECT Customers.CustomerID,  
Customers.CustomerName,  
Orders.OrderID,  
Orders.Product,  
Orders.Amount  
FROM Customers  
LEFT JOIN Orders  
ON Customers.CustomerID = Orders.CustomerID  
UNION  
SELECT Customers.CustomerID,  
Customers.CustomerName,  
Orders.OrderID,  
Orders.Product,  
Orders.Amount  
FROM Customers  
RIGHT JOIN Orders  
ON Customers.CustomerID = Orders.CustomerID;


































